HEADWORD: Exorate
<hw>Ex"o*rate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exoratus</ets>, p. p. of <ets>exorare</ets> to gain by entreaty;
<ets>ex</ets> out, from + <ets>orare</ets> to pay.]</ety> <def>To
persuade, or to gain, by entreaty.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Cockeram.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

